*Using Top-N queries to find top results
 - To find the top N results (like top 10 employees by salary), you can use ORDER BY with DESC to sort the data and then LIMIT or FETCH FIRST to restrict the number of rows returned.
 - LIMIT is widely supported but not part of the SQL standard; FETCH FIRST is the standard SQL alternative.
 - Be aware that using LIMIT or FETCH FIRST may cause the database to process the entire dataset before trimming results, which can impact performance on large tables.

